{"title": "Melancholy Moon", "content": "Removes the colours from our sight\n\nBut we decide which is right\n\nThe Moon. Cold and distant, alone and lifeless... yet, it's the Earth's celestial companion, reflecting light to pierce the pitch black night. So when a character is shown moon gazing, it means he or she shares many of these lunar traits: they are isolated and introspective, melancholy... yet oddly hopeful. All this just by having them look quietly at the moon, or using it as a big old backdrop.\n\nHe or she may have a Tragic Dream, have suffered a Dark and Troubled Past, or have embarked on some new quest that promises to change their life. The trope is also frequently used in love songs.\n\nCan overlap with Weird Moon, often to emphasize the moon. In this case, the moment is used both to establish the world and the character. May also overlap with The Sacred Darkness, particularly when a full moon is paired with a clear starry night, creating an atmosphere of mystery and wonder.\n\nContrast Watching the Sunset and Cue the Sun.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MelancholyMoon", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FragileDreamsFarewellRuinsOfTheMoon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/TheMoodyBlues", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/NeonGenesisEvangelion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Beck", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DarkerThanBlack", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/HeatGuyJ", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MobileSuitGundamWing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ScottMcNeil", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/MarkHildreth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/CardcaptorSakura", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Berserk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Berserk2016", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/SailorMoonCrystal", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/JackToMameNoKi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/JackAndTheBeanstalk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/WhenMarnieWasThere", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/TenchiMuyo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MakotoShinkai", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime